    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        CycleIF getValue(PeriodIF movementPeriod,
                 TimeInstantIF instant)
        This method returns a 'CycleIF' which is valid at the passed time instant within the period of the movement of this 'MovableCycleIF'.
        If the 'CycleIF' degenerates at the passed time instant, the returned 'CycleIF' will be undefined.
        Parameters:
        movementPeriod - - the period in which the movement of this cycle is defined
        instant - - time instant
        Returns:
        a defined 'CycleIF' which is valid at the passed instant, otherwise the returned 'CycleIF' is undefined
